<div class="iDevice_wrapper FreeTextIdevice" id="id254">
<div class="iDevice emphasis0">
<div id="ta254_85" class="block iDevice_content">
<div class="dentro_contenidos" style="display: block;" id="pagina_1">
<p>If/ unless + past simple, ... would/ could/ might + infinitive</p>
<p><i>EX: If I had a lot of money, I would travel around the world</i></p>
<p><i>If I wasn</i>’<i>t so busy I could help you</i></p>
<p>The second conditional is used to express a present or future condition which is imaginary, contrary to the facts, impossible or improbable.</p>
<p><i>If he studied he would pass the exam (he</i>’<i>s not studying)</i></p>
<p><i>If I was a famous actress I</i>’<i>d live in Hollywood. (imaginary)</i></p>
